            "no_electoral_majority_message": "''",
            "description_as_running_mate": "<i>Growing up, I was told I could be anything I wanted to be. There were no limitations restraining me just because I was a girl. Then I joined the military.</i><p>Martha McSally is like you in a lot of ways. She started out fairly moderate in the House before pivoting to the right in recent years. She was also appointed to your friend John McCain's seat after he died and then Jon Kyl resigned. She isn't the most popular of all time since she nearly lost her Senate race in 2022, but she is more popular among MAGA supporters. She can help unite the Republican Party on immigration, an issue where you've been very moderate, as well as helping keep somewhat blue-trending Arizona red this year. Not to mention, like you, she is an Air Force veteran and the first American woman to fly in combat, before earning the rank of colonel. McSally would also be the first female Vice President, but some fear she is too close to Sarah Palin for their liking.</p>",
