            "electoral_victory_message": "''",
            "electoral_loss_message": "''",
            "no_electoral_majority_message": "''",
            "description_as_running_mate": "<i>Based on what our country stands for. We can't fail to stand for democracy.</i><p>Kelly Ayotte would be a very interesting choice this year. She is a conservative Northeastern Republican woman and has served in the Senate for two terms in New Hampshire before narrowly losing to Colin Van Ostern in 2022. She is still a popular figure among moderates, and can help in her battleground home state this year. She is also a strong fiscal conservative, which could unite the Republican Party on economic issues outside of protectionism. Kelly Ayotte was a staunch ally of the Schwarzenegger administration in the Senate, and would be the first female Vice President of the United States if elected. There would be a lot of backlash from social conservatives and MAGA supporters, giving Musk a lot of ammunition. But as long as you can replicate you and Arnie's victories, it won't matter in the end.</p>",
