            "electoral_loss_message": "''",
            "no_electoral_majority_message": "''",
            "description_as_running_mate": "<i>I have optimism for the future. You have to.</i><p>A member of the prominent Lujan political dynasty in her home state of New Mexico, Michelle Lujan Grisham has served as the state's Governor since 2019. If elected, she would become the first Latina and the first Female Vice president of the United States. She has been a strong advocate for reproductive rights and still remembers the summer day the Supreme Court nearly overturned <i>Roe v. Wade</i>. She is also a strong advocate for gun reform, and her rather unpopular actions of restrticting firearms in Albuquerque last year will likely be brought up by Republicans. Nevertheless, while her home state of New Mexico is a battleground, it always leaned towards you, but it's good reassurance and she can also help with Latino voters elsewhere, particularly in Nevada and Florida.</p>",
